{
  "video_id": "AGoWL2Vbp1c",
  "title": "A secret about collective nouns - English In A Minute",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 600.0,
      "end_time": 2800.0,
      "text": "Hi, I'm Dan from BBC Learning English"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2800.0,
      "end_time": 6940.0,
      "text": "and today I'm going to tell you something about collective nouns."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 6940.0,
      "end_time": 9380.0,
      "text": "Collective nouns are often called group nouns."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 9380.0,
      "end_time": 13140.0,
      "text": "That is because they represent a number of things together."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 13100.0,
      "end_time": 13980.0,
      "text": "Examples are:"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 13980.0,
      "end_time": 16760.0,
      "text": "government, family and team."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 16760.0,
      "end_time": 17980.0,
      "text": "So, what's the big deal?"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 17980.0,
      "end_time": 20000.0,
      "text": "The special thing about these collective nouns"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 20000.0,
      "end_time": 23220.0,
      "text": "is that they can be singular or plural."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 23220.0,
      "end_time": 26320.0,
      "text": "If you consider your family to be a group of individuals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 26320.0,
      "end_time": 29980.0,
      "text": "then the pronoun is they and the verb is plural."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 29980.0,
      "end_time": 31980.0,
      "text": "My family are happy."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 31990.0,
      "end_time": 35699.0,
      "text": "But your family can also be considered as a single unit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 35700.0,
      "end_time": 38520.0,
      "text": "a machine that all works together."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 38520.0,
      "end_time": 42400.0,
      "text": "In this case, the pronoun is it and the verb is singular."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 42400.0,
      "end_time": 44760.0,
      "text": "My family is happy."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 44760.0,
      "end_time": 47590.0,
      "text": "This does not apply to all collective nouns,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 47600.0,
      "end_time": 48180.0,
      "text": "so be careful."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 48180.0,
      "end_time": 50760.0,
      "text": "Police and staff are always plural."
    }
  ]
}